It probably means what units we use. In SI (metric) units the base 
unit for area is the square meter. Another metric base unit for area  
is the are, which is 100 square meters; land areas are often measured 
in hectares (1 hectare = 100 ares = 1 square hectometer = 0.01 square 
kilometer).

